an\u0131}}''}}\n| [[File:Fahrettin Koca 20200311 2.jpg|100px]]\n| {{nobr|[[Fahrettin Koca]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n| [[Ministry of National Education (Turkey)|Ministry of National Education]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|Mill\u00ee E\u011fitim Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n| [[File:Ziya Sel\u00e7uk (cropped).jpg|100px]]\n| {{nobr|[[Ziya Sel\u00e7uk]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n| [[Ministry of National Defence (Turkey)|Ministry of National Defence]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|Mill\u00ee Savunma Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n| [[File:Hulusi Akar MSC 2019 (cropped 2).jpg|100px]]\n| {{nobr|[[Hulusi Akar]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n| [[Ministry of Science, Industry and Technology (Turkey)|Ministry of Industry and Technology]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|Sanayi ve Teknoloji Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n| [[File:Mustafa Varank.jpg|100px]]\n| {{nobr|[[Mustafa Varank]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n| [[Ministry of Labour and Social Security (Turkey)|Ministry of Labour, Social Services and Family]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|\u00c7al\u0131\u015fma, Sosyal Hizmetler ve Aile Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n| \n| {{nobr|[[Zehra Z\u00fcmr\u00fct Sel\u00e7uk]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Ministry of Transport, Maritime and Communication (Turkey)|Ministry of Transport and Infrastructure]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|Ula\u015ft\u0131rma ve Altyap\u0131 Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n| [[File:Mehmet Cahit Turhan - 2019 (cropped).jpg|100px]]\n| {{nobr|[[Mehmet Cahit Turhan]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 28 March 2020\n|-\n| [[File:Adil Karaismailo\u011flu (cropped).jpg|100px]]\n| {{nobr|[[Adil Karaismailo\u011flu]]}} \n| Independent\n| 28 March 2020 \u2013 present    \n|-   \n| style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n| [[Ministry of Youth and Sports (Turkey)|Ministry of Youth and Sports]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|Gen\u00e7lik ve Spor Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n|\n| {{nobr|[[Mehmet Kasapo\u011flu]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n| [[Ministry of Customs and Trade (Turkey)|Ministry of Trade]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|Ticaret Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n| \n| {{nobr|[[Ruhsar Pekcan]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" | \n| [[Ministry of Environment and Urban Planning (Turkey)|Ministry of Environment and Urban Planning]]<br>{{small|''{{lang|tr|\u00c7evre ve \u015eehircilik Bakan\u0131}}''}}\n|\n| {{nobr|[[Murat Kurum]]}}\n| Independent\n| 10 July 2018 \u2013 present\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Erdogan Cabinet}}\n[[Category:Government of Turkey]]\n[[Category:2018 in Turkish politics]]\n[[Category:2018 establishments in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Cabinets established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Cabinets of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Members of the 66th government of Turkey| ]]\n\n{{Cabinet Erdo\u011fan IV}}\n{{Cabinets of Turkey}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox government cabinet\n| cabinet_name            = Fourth Erdo\u011fan Cabinet<br>{{small|''D\u00f6rd\u00fcnc\u00fc Erdo\u011fan H\u00fck\u00fcmeti''}}\n| jurisdiction            = Turkey\n| cabinet_number          = 66th\n| flag                    = Flag_of_Turkey.svg\n| incumbent               = 9 July 2018\n| image                   = Recep Tayyip Erdogan 2017.jpg\n| date_formed             = 10 July 2018\n| date_dissolved          = \n| government_head         = [[Recep Tayyip Erdo\u011fan]]\n| deputy government_head  = \n| government_head_history =\n| state_head              = [[Recep Tayyip Erdo\u011fan]]\n| current_number          = \n| former_members_number   =\n| total_number            = \n| political_party         = [[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|Justice and Development Party]]<br>[[Independent politician|Independent(s)]]\n| legislature_status      = {{Longitem|[[Minority government|Minority]]<br /><small>''with [[People's Alliance (Turkey)|MHP and BBP confidence & supply]]''</small>}}\n| opposition_cabinet      =\n| opposition_party        = [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|Republican People's Party]] <br/> [[\u0130yi Parti|Good Party]]\n| opposition_leader       = [[Kemal K\u0131l\u0131\u00e7daro\u011flu]]\n| election                = \n| legislature_term        =\n| outgoing_formation      =\n| previous                = [[Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m Cabinet]]\n| successor               = \n}}\n\nThe '''Fourth Erdo\u011fan Cabinet''' is the 66th government of the [[Turkey|Republic of Turkey]], which was declared on 9 July 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=President Erdo\u011fan announces ministers of Turkey's new cabinet |url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/president-erdogan-announces-ministers-of-turkeys-new-cabinet-134375 |website=H\u00fcrriyet Daily News |accessdate=10 July 2018 |language=en}}</ref> It is the first cabinet after Turkey's transition into [[presidential republic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Erdogan announces first cabinet under new presidential system |url=https://www.trtworld.com/turkey/erdogan-announces-first-cabinet-under-new-presidential-system-18792 |website=[[TRT World]] |accessdate=10 July 2018 |language=tr-TR}}</ref> It was also the first cabinet that did not require [[Grand National Assembly of Turkey|parliamentary]] approval to be formed.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Editorial |first1=Reuters |title=Turkey's Erdogan to name cabinet as signals action on economy |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-turkey-politics-erdogan/turkeys-erdogan-to-name-cabinet-as-signals-action-on-economy-idUSKBN1JX0D1 |website=U.S. |accessdate=10 July 2018 |quote=...Erdogan will select his own cabinet and regulate ministries and remove civil servants, all without parliamentary approval. ...}}</ref>\n\n==Changes==\nIn this new system, the number of ministries were reduced to 16 from 26. A statutory decree was issued to merge several ministries, and also to abolish certain organizational and functional laws of some ministries and institutions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Turkey: Decree out making first changes in new system |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/todays-headlines/turkey-decree-out-making-first-changes-in-new-system/1199042 |website=Anadolu Agency |accessdate=15 July 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Previous name\n! Current name\n|-\n| Ministry of Labour and Social Security\n| rowspan=2 valign=center|Ministry of Labour, Social Services and Family\n|-\n| Ministry of Family and Social Policy\n|-\n| Ministry of Science, Industry and Technology\n| rowspan=2 valign=center|Ministry of Industry and Technology\n|-\n| Ministry of Development\n|-\n| Ministry of Customs and Trade\n| rowspan=2 valign=center|Ministry of Trade\n|-\n| Ministry of Economic Affairs\n|-\n| Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock\n| rowspan=2 valign=center|Ministry of Agriculture and Forest\n|-\n| Ministry of Forest and Water Management\n|-\n| Ministry of Finance\n| Ministry of Finance and Treasury\n|-\n| Ministry of Transport, Maritime and Communication\n| Ministry of Transport and Infrastructure\n|-\n| Ministry of European Union Affairs\n| ''Merged into the Ministry of Foreign Affairs''\n|}\n\n==Composition==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"| Function !! Portrait !! Incumbent !! Party !!  In office\n|-\n|-\n| style=\"background: {{Justice and Development Party (Turkey)/meta/color}}\" | \n| bgcolor=#DDDDDD | '''[[President of Turkey|President]]'''<br>{{small|'''''{{lang|tr|Cumhurba\u015fkan\u0131}}'''''}}\n| bgcolor=#DDDDDD | [[File:Recep Tayyip Erdogan 2017.jpg|100px]]\n| b